ANOTHER wild animal is on the loose in the North West. A lioness escaped on Wednesday, 23 February, as it was being transported from one farm to another on the Beesdam Road between Stella and Tlakgameng in Vryburg. Nature Conservation and farmers are on the lookout for the wild animal. ALSO READ: Farmers hit hard by floods Police spokeswoman Capitan Aafje Botma said the owner of the two lions in transit discovered that a female had escaped when he arrived in Tlakgameng. Communities around Setlakgole and Tlakgameng are urged to contact Nature Conservation on 082 563 7763/ 0734467452 / 0813366882,  or their local police station if they see the lioness.